text.tspan: (with inverted y-axis, assuming 60*60 pixel unit boxes with the dashed red line)
x shifts (NE vs. SW) direction; +1 x -> +30 width, +15 height; -1 x -> -30 width, -15 height
y shifts (NW vs. SE) direction; +1 y -> -30 width, +15 height; -1 y -> +30 width, -15 height
z shifts (N vs. S) direction; +1 z -> no width change, +60 height; -1 z -> no width change, -60 height
